(:summary    "A major mode for editing Mustache files"
 :repository (git . "git://github.com/mustache/emacs.git")
 :license    "GPL-2"
 :authors    (("Tony Gentilcore")
	      ("Chris Wanstrath")
	      ("Daniel Hackney"))
 :maintainer ("Tony Gentilcore")
 :provided   (mustache-mode)
 :required   ((("emacs" font-lock)))
 :homepage   "https://github.com/mustache/emacs"
 :commentary "\
1) Copy this file somewhere in your Emacs `load-path'.  To see what
   your `load-path' is, run inside emacs: C-h v load-path<RET>

2) Add the following to your .emacs file:

   (require 'mustache-mode)

While the Mustache language can be used for any types of text,
this mode is intended for using Mustache to write HTML.")
